definition.value: A start strain point is the data point with the lowest abscissa value on a line between two points on a stress-strain curve. [Allotrope]
An end strain point is the data point with the highest abscissa value on a line between two points on a stress-strain curve. [Allotrope]
A secant modulus aggregate document is a document that is about a collection of secant modulus documents. [Allotrope]
A secant modulus document is a document that encompasses the information associated with a secant modulus. [Allotrope]
A secant modulus is the slope of a line from the origin of a stress-strain curve intersecting at a given strain value. [Allotrope]
A strain is a quality quantification facet that quantifies the magnitude of deformation representing the displacement between particles in the body relative to a reference length. [Allotrope]
A stress is a quality quantification facet that quantifies the internal forces that neighboring particles of a continuous material exert on each other. [Allotrope]
A humidity (datum) is a quantity facet that quantifies some humidity. [Allotrope]
A sampling orientation code is a code that indicates a sampling orientation. [Allotrope]
A width datum is a quality quantification facet that quantifies a 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance from one side of an object to another side which is opposite. [Allotrope]
A force datum is a quality quantification facet that quantifies the physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's rate of change of momentum. [Allotrope]
A stress-strain data cube is a data cube that represents a stress-strain curve. [Allotrope]
A stress-strain curve is a data distribution function that is a plot of the stress vs strain of a material. [Allotrope]
A code scan result is an assay result that is the output of a code scanning. [Allotrope]
A device response signal is a signal that is sent by some device as a result of some prior communication. [Allotrope]
A gas chromatography aggregate document is a document that aggregates gas chromatography documents. [Allotrope]
A gas chromatography document is a document that encompasses the information associated with a gas chromatography run. [Allotrope]
A chromatography column document is a document that encompasses the information associated with a chromatography column. [Allotrope]
A chromatography column fill type is a classification datum that classifies a chromatography column by the form of the stationary phase in the column. [Allotrope]
A chromatography column film thickness is a thickness datum that quantifies the thickness of the film coating in a chromatography column. [Allotrope]
A sampling type is a classification datum that classifies the type of sampling approach used to take a sample. [Allotrope]
A detector distance setting is the distance between the ultrasonic sensor of the foam qualification device and the bottom of a test container during a baseline measurement. [Allotrope]
A measurement start delay setting is a control setting that specifies a delay before starting a measurement process. [Allotrope]
An ambient pressure is a quantity facet that quantifies the pressure of the surrounding atmosphere. [Allotrope]

Relative humidity is the ratio, often expressed as a percentage, of the partial pressure of water in the atmosphere at some observed temperature, to the saturation vapor pressure of pure water at this temperature. [IUPAC]
A polyol reservoir temperature is a quantity facet that quantifies the temperature of a reservoir containing polyol. [Allotrope]
A reservoir temperature is a quantity facet that quantifies the temperature of some reservoir. [Allotrope]
A isocyanate reservoir temperature is a quantity facet that quantifies the temperature of a reservoir containing isocyanate. [Allotrope]
A plate temperature is a quality quantification facet that quantifies the temperature of some plate. [Allotrope]
A plate heater temperature is a quality quantification facet that quantifies the temperature of some plate heater. [Allotrope]
A dielectric polarization field frequency setting is a control setting that specifies the frequency of the electrical field used for dielectric polarization of a sample. [Allotrope]
A reaction duration is a duration that indicates the time taken for a reaction to complete. [Allotrope]
A force gauge type is a classification datum that classifies some force gauge by its rated force calibration. [Allotrope]
A container shape is a classification datum that classifies the shape of some container. [Allotrope]
A container height is a height of some container. [Allotrope]
A container diameter is a diameter of some container. [Allotrope]
A process termination state type is a classification facet that classifies the process state at the end of a process. [Allotrope]
A start height is the height of some entity at the start of a process. [Allotrope]
An end height is the height of some entity at the end of a process. [Allotrope]
A velocity is a quality quantification facet that quantifies some velocity. [Allotrope]
A gel time is the time at which a material's state of matter transitions into a gel. [Allotrope]
A foam profile data cube is a data cube that represents a foam profile. [Allotrope]
The electric displacement vector and the product of the electric field strength with the permittivity of vacuum. [IUPAC]
A viscosity is a quality quantification facet that quantifies the viscosity of a fluid. [Allotrope]
A foam profile is a profile that quantifies the properties of a foam over time. [Allotrope]
A mass spectrometry aggregate document is a document that aggregates mass spectrometry documents. [Allotrope]
A sample introduction document is a document that encompasses the information associated with the process of sample introduction. [Allotrope]
A sample introduction mode setting is a control setting that specifies the type of sample introduction process to be used, which is the process of loading the sample into a system. [Allotrope]
A laser firing frequency setting is a control setting that specifies the frequency of firing of a laser. [Allotrope]
A sample introduction description is a description that describes the process of sample introduction. [Allotrope]
